#: ../../manual/editors/3dview/object/transform/transform_control/pivot_point/individual_origins.rst:101
msgid ""
"Once you are aware of its limitations and pitfalls, this tool can save a "
"lot of time and lead to unique shapes. This \"anemone\" was modeled from "
"a 12 sided cylinder in about 10 minutes by repeatedly using this "
"workflow: extrusions of individual faces, scaling with *median as a pivot"
" point*, and scaling and rotations of those faces with *Individual "
"Origins as pivot points*."
msgstr ""

